h3. Issue Summary
In the permission scheme of a project, when trying to grant a single user under a permission, if the user has been renamed, it will not be possible to include the user in that.

h3. Steps to Reproduce
# Rename a user;
# Go to a permission scheme, and choose a permission to edit;
# Under *Granted to*, select the *Sinlge user* option;
# Search for the renamed user;
# Click on *Grant*;

h3. Expected Results
The user will receive that permission.

h3. Actual Results
The user will not receive the permission.
* Error message on the UI:
{code}This combination of permission and people just won't work

User <user-info> does not exist{code}

h3. Workaround
Create a group for that permission, and add the user impacted on this group. Grant a group permission for the group.

h3.Summary

